If I'm going to indulge my unholy love of macaroni at the expense of my millennially lactose-sensitive stomach, possibly shortening my lifespan in the process, I want it to be good. This place delivers.  At $7 for a "value sized" mac - at least a meal's worth - it's good value for money, and cheesy as all heck. The crust was crunchy, the noodles al dente (I suspect they were cooked, or at least sauced, on the spot). The woman behind the counter, who was possibly also the sole cook, was extremely nice. I opted for the Classic, but I can't wait to go back and try some of the other cheese combinations and the vegan options.  Is there room for improvement? Sure. It would have been nice to have some more sauce options, or at least salt and pepper. I personally prefer a soupier béchamel and a more judicious approach to cheese. But let me tell you, when I was marching down Fulton Street on a grim, icy Tuesday night and this place swam into view - warm and glowing amidst the shuttered storefronts - I felt heaven was smiling upon me.

I've gone to this place three times since it's been open. One out of three times I received edible food. The first time I went, they'd just opened and the food was okay. Not amazing, but just okay. The second time I visited was about a year later. Unfortunately the entire dish was burned, and tasted like nothing but burned material. It even stunk up my house. I had to throw the whole thing out & take the garbage out too.  I've visited for a third time, now a couple of years after the second time. Firstly, I've never seen the store so dirty. It was empty, it seemed they had no orders coming in, yet the floor was sticky & the paint job in combination is making the place look really dreary. Well, the food wasn't burned this time, at least. It's just that the food literally tastes like water. There's no seasoning whatsoever on it, the actual macaroni have no sauce whatsoever on them, and the whole thing tastes like not even a pinch of salt was used. I waited way too long for the dish to be finished to get this tasteless plate.  My best suggestion to anyone considering going here is to simply go to the grocery store a couple of blocks away, buy the ingredients, go home and make it yourself, from a recipe on the internet. This was an utter waste of time and $10.00 for me tonight. Never again.

1/20/16 Delivery took over 2 hours today and they're barely a mile away. I ordered through GrubHub at 3PM and the food did not arrive until 5:30PM. Their excuse when I called after 2 hours of waiting was that they had messed up my vegan mac and cheese the first time and hadn't made them vegan so had to remake them. I still don't see how this makes anything 2 hours long of a wait??🤔  I ordered the 1 small Vegan Veggie Mac and 1 small Vegan Jerk Mac. My friend ordered 1 large Buffalo Mac. While he enjoyed his mac and cheese I would NOT order from here again, at least delivery. I have been excited to try some other vegan mac and cheese however everything was WAY over spiced. The salty taste in the Vegan Veggie was so overpowering that I had to mix it with the Vegan Jerk Mac. I was also upset that my friends Mac came with breadcrumbs but mine didn't? If the bread crumbs aren't vegan there are so many panko breadcrumbs out there that have no egg in it.  Also the prices are ridiculous. To pay $20 for a large or $10-14 for a small is ridiculous. And the charging so much for added toppings.  If you are vegan I'd recommend you go to either "S,MAC Saritas Mac And Cheese" (I found it a bit pricy for the portion size and dry usually so was looking for something new) in the city or travel to Queens and get the Vegan Mac and Cheese from "Veggie Castle II" (by far the best and creamiest Vegan Mac and cheese and Mac and cheese I've ever had hands down in my opinion) and you can get a whole takeout plate of yummy vegan options for less than $20.  Maybe it was just a bad day for them so I'd possibly give it another go in person but again, I've seen other reviews claiming the same delivery issues, put on a Lord of The Rings movie if you want delivery. It should arrive during the credits...🙄  2/5 And only the 2 stars for my friend enjoying his Mac and cheese and for the effort of having vegan options on the menu.  **Also I called and informed the store of this but to this day on GrubHub it says you guy's vegan options are "Temporarily Unavailable" and it's been like this for at least 6 months. You're losing customers due to not changing this btw...

I WANTED the large and would've bought it at a $12/$13 price point but that was just Outrageous. The shrimp were not even big why does only mac cost practically $10?
